Data Format: 
One table per dataset. The observational units of most of these tables correspond to patients. One unit is one patient, or person, responding to the survey. There are many many many rows corresponding to different people. There are many many many columns corresponding to different questions asked of subjects (ex. Race, gender, location, mental conditions, etc.) 